### 03 — Body & content-type examples (BodyExampleController)
# Watch the Content-Type (what you send) and Accept (what you want back) headers.

@host = http://localhost:8081

### 1) Plain text in & out
POST {{host}}/examples/echo-text
Content-Type: text/plain

hello there, this is raw text

### 2) JSON in & out
POST {{host}}/examples/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sara",
  "message": "hi"
}

### 3) XML in & out
POST {{host}}/examples/xml
Content-Type: application/xml
Accept: application/xml

<Greeting>
  <name>Sara</name>
  <message>hi</message>
</Greeting>

### 4a) Same endpoint, ask for JSON (Accept header)
GET {{host}}/examples/greeting?name=Sara
Accept: application/json

### 4b) Same endpoint, ask for XML — identical URL, different Accept
GET {{host}}/examples/greeting?name=Sara
Accept: application/xml

### 5) Form data (application/x-www-form-urlencoded)
POST {{host}}/examples/form
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

name=Sara&message=hello from a form

### 6a) Same path /flexible — routed to the JSON method by Content-Type
POST {{host}}/examples/flexible
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Sara", "message": "x" }

### 6b) Same path /flexible — routed to the TEXT method by Content-Type
POST {{host}}/examples/flexible
Content-Type: text/plain

just some text

### 7a) Download raw bytes (octet-stream)
GET {{host}}/examples/download

### 7b) Upload a file (multipart/form-data)
POST {{host}}/examples/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="hello.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

the contents of the uploaded file
--WebAppBoundary--

### 8) Echo anything — reports the Content-Type and raw body it received
POST {{host}}/examples/echo
Content-Type: application/json

{ "anything": true }

### 9) Real-world create: 201 + Location header, body as XML (via Accept)
POST {{host}}/examples/tickets
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/xml

{
  "title": "Printer broken",
  "severity": "high"
}
